# ============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================================================
# 1. ENVIRONMENT FILES:
#    - Copy .env.example to .env.local or .env.development
#    - NEVER commit any .env files with credentials
#    - Use .env.example as a template for documentation
#
# 2. SECRETS:
#    - API Keys, tokens, and credentials must NEVER be committed
#    - Use environment variables for all sensitive data
#    - Consider using Supabase Vault for production secrets
#
# 3. BUILD ARTIFACTS:
#    - dist/, build/, .next/ are generated and should never be committed
#    - These are rebuilt during deployment
#
# 4. SENSITIVE FILES:
#    - Service account keys, private keys, certificates
#    - Firebase config, database credentials, API tokens
#
# 5. IDE AND OS FILES:
#    - .vscode/, .idea/ (except extensions.json which can be shared)
#    - .DS_Store, Thumbs.db, and other OS-specific files
#
# If you accidentally committed sensitive files:
#    git rm --cached <filename>
#    git commit -m "Remove <filename>"
#    git push
